The paper deals with a method for truncating Gaussian distributed variables, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The method involves moment-based Gaussian approximations, which is a technique used in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG, cs.AI). The motivating problem for the method is Kalman filtering, which is a common topic in control systems and robotics (cs.SY, cs.NE).
